data.description: You’ll love the layout of this side-by-side duplex in the Poly High neighborhood, perfect for an investor or an owner-occupant looking to help pay the mortgage with rental income from the second unit. With 1639 total square feet, both of the 1-bedroom, 1-bath units are quite spacious. Built in 1941, this home features wood siding, a detached garage with separate doors for each unit, and a prime location just steps from California Recreation Park and Long Beach Polytechnic High School.   Inside the first unit you’ll find a spacious living room with beautiful wood floors and plenty of natural light. The ample windows have plantation shutters for privacy and energy efficiency. Off the living room is a formal dining room that could also be used as a home office. The redone kitchen features tile flooring, granite counters, plenty of cabinet space and a stackable washer and dryer that is included in the sale. A small hallway with lots of built-in storage connects to the spacious bedroom and full bath. There is a brand new hot water heater as well.  The second unit also features a large living room. It has tile flooring which extends down the hallway, leading to the bright and airy kitchen. Here you’ll find classic black-and-white checkered floor tile, a brand new 5-burner range and hookups for a stackable washer and gas dryer.  Across the hall is a spacious bedroom with mirrored closet doors.  A bonus room that could be used as a second bedroom or home office is off the kitchen and has wood flooring, a ceiling fan and plantation shutters.  There is also additional built-in storage in the hallway leading to the full bathroom.  Off the small private back patio, there is a separate laundry room.  A long gated driveway with two individual garage spaces provides plenty of off street parking.  Back on market. Buyer could not get loan! Their loss is your opportunity!
